D).\n71\t \n72\t@@ -52,6 +76,14 @@ When the judge edits source (`git -C sdk/org diff …`), before committing:\n73\t 2. **No overfitting.** Grep the diff for scenario literals (persona names, fixture facts, this\n74\t    scenario's table names) — any is an automatic reject:\n75\t    `git -C sdk/org diff <files> | grep -iE '^\\+' | grep -iE '<persona|place|token|number>'`.\n76\t+   **The grep is necessary but not sufficient** — also READ the added prose for scenario-DOMAIN\n77\t+   framing, which no grep catches: a travel scenario's fix that teaches THING about \"itineraries\" /\n78\t+   \"destinations\", a cooking one about \"recipes\", etc. bends a system-wide brain toward this one\n79\t+   story's domain and is overfit just as badly as a literal. Demand the domain-NEUTRAL principle (the\n80\t+   real Tanzania fix: not \"list each destination in an itinerary\" but \"a distinct part with few facts\n81\t+   still gets its own specialist; brevity is not a reason to merge\"). Test each added sentence: could\n82\t+   it have come from a scenario in a completely different domain? If not, reject — send it back or\n83\t+   rewrite it yourself before committing.\n84\t 3. **Verified.** The report must show a fresh `--fresh-server --through <N>` replay where the failed\n85\t    step (and everything before it) passes. An honest partial-FAIL is fine (next round continues);\n86\t    a fake PASS is not.\n87\tdiff --git a/automation/instances/scenario-campaign/config.mjs b/automation/instances/scenario-campaign/config.mjs\n88\tindex 66170de9..32cdb8ee 100644\n89\t--- a/automation/instances/scenario-campaign/config.mjs\n90\t+++ b/automation/instances/scenario-campaign/config.mjs\n91\t@@ -29,13 +29,10 @@ export default {\n92\t \n93\t   // Each task is a scenario id under sdk/org/scenarios/. Round 1 baselines + adds the first new\n94\t   // Acts; later rounds add more. Append new scenario ids here to fold them in (they start at round 1).\n95\t+  // One scenario at a time (human-gated, serial). Keep only the ACTIVE scenario here; when it goes\n96\t+  // fully green, replace it with the next one (06-tanzania → 07-life-admin → …).\n97\t   tasks: [\n98\t-    '05-latam',\n99\t     '06-tanzania',\n100\t-    '07-life-admin',\n101\t-    '08-small-shop',\n102\t-    '09-home-renovation',\n103\t-    '10-family-recipes',\n104\t   ],\n105\t \n106\t   // Every round runs the judge; it decides internally whether to FIX the first failure (and verify)\n107\tdiff --git a/automation/instances/scenario-campaign/judge.md b/automation/instances/scenario-campaign/judge.md\n108\tindex aacf53e1..4f03fa41 100644\n109\t--- a/automation/instances/scenario-campaign/judge.md\n110\t+++ b/automation/instances/scenario-campaign/judge.md\n111\t@@ -46,10 +46,16 @@ Everything runs LOCAL against a throwaway `lmthing serve` (budget-free Azure key\n112\t        done\n113\t        echo \"still waiting for step $S (~8m) — RUN THE POLL AGAIN, do not stop\"\n114\t \n115\t-   Read the returned `step-NN.json` (delegates / yields / errors / reply, the asks, and the real\n116\t-   spaces + app tables + DB rows), JUDGE it against that step's `expect` + the invariants, then poll\n117\t-   the NEXT step (`S=02`, `S=03`, …). Each poll blocks ≤ ~8 min, safely under the cap; if it prints\n118\t-   \"still waiting\", run it again. `trace.md` carries the same evidence in prose with the checklist.\n119\t+   Read the returned `step-NN.json` — it is the COMPACT observables you score: space names +\n120\t+   `spaceCount`, app tables as `{name: rowCount}`, per-turn `delegates` / `yieldKinds` / `yieldCount`\n121\t+   / `errors` / `lastText` (the reply), and the `asks`. That is enough to judge almost every `expect`.\n122\t+   JUDGE it against that step's `expect` + the invariants, then poll the NEXT step (`S=02`, `S=03`, …).\n123\t+   **Do NOT read `step-NN.full.json` by default** — it is the raw dump (every DB row, every yield's\n124\t+   args) and reading it repeatedly is what exhausts your context and ki