{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_89cSNhnqZqoFGBmstPjI1JIf","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: inventory\n3\toutput:\n4\t  scopes: array\n5\trole: explore\n6\tfunctions: []\n7\t---\n8\t\n9\tIdentify every independently owned scope in the supplied material. `request`, `sourceSummary`,\n10\t`attachmentIds`, and `specialistFacts` are in scope. First read every supplied document with\n11\t`readDocument`; source text is authoritative over the short summary. A scope has its own facts and\n12\tdeserves a later answer boundary; do not merge it into a broad overview because it has few facts. A\n13\tscope is a stable part of the user's material (such as a location, stage, person, client, or piece of\n14\tequipment), NOT an individual expense, note, reminder, fact, photo, memory, shared overview, or\n15\tcross-cutting finance grouping. Combine subparts only when they are one uninterrupted operational\n16\tstage; otherwise give each independently owned location or stage its own scope. Include every stable\n17\tscope represented in the source, not only the most detailed ones.\n18\t\n19\tFor each scope, emit `{ topic, goal, research }`, where `research` is a JSON-stringifiable object\n20\twith `topic`, `executive_summary`, `findings`, `conclusion`, and `sources`. Ground its findings only\n21\tin the supplied document text and `specialistFacts`; sources must be empty because supplied material\n22\tis not web research. Emit these statements across turns:\n23\t\n24\tconst documents = await Promise.all((attachmentIds as string[]).map((id) => readDocument(id)));\n25\t\n26\tcurrentTask.resolve({ scopes: [{ topic: \"<scope>\", goal: \"<what it should answer>\", research: { topic: \"<scope>\", executive_summary: \"<summary>\", findings: [{ heading: \"<facet>\", detail: \"<supplied facts>\" }], conclusion: \"\", sources: [] } }] });"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ab76f4c6-b375-4c4c-a705-ee82d5ccb7a7","uuid":"b1b99a84-808a-41ee