E place — an app you can open on your phone with the costs, the itinerary, the key contacts, and the per-topic details (park rules, tipping norms, what you bought where). Want me to pull all of this together into an app right here, organized and searchable?\\\"]}]}\",\n      \"delegates\": [\n        \"system-vision/vision\",\n        \"system-files/dispatch\",\n        \"system-files/reader\",\n        \"system-files/sheet\"\n      ],\n      \"yieldKinds\": [\n        \"delegate\",\n        \"loadKnowledge\",\n        \"readDocument\",\n        \"setSessionMeta\"\n      ],\n      \"yieldCount\": 15,\n      \"errors\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"typecheck_error\",\n          \"message\": \"Conversion of type 'Promise<any>' to type 'string' may be a mistake because neither type sufficiently overlaps with the other. If this was intentional, convert the expression to 'unknown' first.; Conversion of type 'Promise<any>' to type 'string' may be a mistake because neither type sufficiently overlaps with the other. If this was intentional, convert the expression to 'unknown' first.\",\n          \"statement\": \"// Delegate to the vision specialist and files dispatcher for all attachments at once.\\nconst [seen, fileAnswer] = await Promise.all([\\n  delegate('system-vision', 'vision', {\\n    query: 'Describe the photo of Stone Town, Zanzibar — what do you see? Keep it brief, a couple of sentences capturing the key subject and atmosphere.',\\n    attachmentIds: ['b889826f-f6ae-47fc-8b62-7168af04a519'],\\n  }) as string,\\n  delegate('system-files', 'dispatch', {\\n    query: 'Summarize these three documents for me — tanzaniamemories.md (notes), trip-costs.xlsx (spreadsheet), ngorongoro-conservation-area-tariffs.pdf (park fees). For each, give a short summary of what it covers, and list the concrete specifics I need to plan around: names, numbers, dates, costs, payment statuses, reference codes. I need enough detail to build an app and to populate per-topic knowledge