ract,system-spaces-dag}.test.ts` · verify=**INCONCLUSIVE (ran out of context again)** · **DEEPER ROOT CAUSE found, past the L2 structure:** `organize_material`'s fan-out is WORKING — it enumerated all legs and fired all 5 architect delegates in parallel. But the architect's **action prompt manually CONTINUES after a tasklist result the runtime already auto-captures**; under the parallel `forEach`, that invalid cross-turn continuation clobbers sibling results → only the LAST architect build registers (some reruns instead over-produced 10 spaces w/ duplicate/overview junk — same bug, other face). R10 started the fix (delete the manual continuation, rely on the action runtime's envelope return) + updated both tests, but died of `Prompt is too long` before verifying.\n- **Context fix (human, after R10):** rounds 9 AND 10 both died of context exhaustion because\n  `step-NN.json` was an ~80KB full dump (every DB row + every yield's args) that the judge re-read\n  across reruns. FIXED: `run-yaml.mjs` now writes a ~10× smaller COMPACT `step-NN.json` (observables:\n  space names+count, table row-counts, delegate/yield kinds, errors, reply) and spills the raw dump to\n  `step-NN.full.json`; judge.md tells the judge to read compact by default. This should let a round\n  finish.\n- **Direction (human, after R10):** the architect action-contract fix is IN THE TREE (unverified). DO\n  NOT re-attribute — the diagnosis is solid (parallel architect results clobbered by the redundant\n  manual continuation). Rebuild, run ONE clean `--through 2` verify, and confirm ALL legs build ONCE\n  (no clobber → all present; no over-production → no duplicate/overview spaces). ⚠️ HIGH BLAST RADIUS:\n  the architect action contract drives EVERY space build product-wide — confirm the two updated tests\n  pass and that a SINGLE (non-parallel) `build_specialist` still returns its result. If verify is\n  green, step 2 is finally done → continue to step 3.\n- R11 · step 2 · (traced, no runtime edit) · verify=**INCONCLUSIVE (context death again)** · with R10's fix in the tree, step 2 swung the OTHER way: **17 fragmented spaces** (\"Cairo Stopover 1\", \"Cairo Stopover 1 Arrival\", \"Cairo Stopover 2\", \"Arusha Pre-Safari\", \"Arusha Post-Safari\", \"Suricata Booking\" + \"Suricata Circuit\", …) — the organizer RE-ENTERS / over-fragments. The judge was reaching for an **L3 action-runtime** change and died before writing it (no `src` runtime edit landed — the tree is still just the L2 tasklist + architect prompt + tests).\n- **ROOT CAUSE (human, after R11 — high confidence, verified by reading the prompt):** it is NOT an\n  L3 runtime bug. `user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md` has **TWO overlapping build paths for supplied\n  material that both fire**: (1) path 3 (~L394–417) \"build each space DIRECTLY\" via an inline per-part\n  `delegate('system-architect','architect','synthesize_and_run')` loop, and (2) path 4a (~L458)\n  `tasklist('organize_material')` which ALREADY does inventory → per-scope specialist → app — AND THEN\n  (~L465–472) STILL says \"build the spaces too… Build the parts first, then the app\", duplicating what\n  organize_material just did. So THING runs organize_material AND the manual per-part build → double\n  build → re-entry / 17 fragments (and, when the manual path wins a race, the R10 clobber symptom).\n- **Direction (human, after R11):** make `organize_material` the SINGLE supplied-material build path.\n  In `thing/instruct.md`: on the \"supplied material + yes\" path, call `organize_material` and REPORT\n  its result — DELETE the competing manual per-part build guidance (the L465–472 \"build the parts\n  first, then the app\" prose, and steer path 3's inline `synthesize_and_run` loop to NON-supplied\n  single-space requests only). This is **L1**, one file, a deletion — do NOT touch the action runtime\n  (L3). Then RE-EXAMINE whether R10's architect continuation-removal is still needed with a single\n  path (it may have been chasing a symptom of the double-build; keep it only if a single-path verify\n  still shows a genuine parallel-clobber). Context death is fixed (compact `step-NN.json`), so ONE\n  clean `--through 2` verify should finish: expect ONE specialist per leg (Cairo, Dar, Zanzibar/Stone\n  Town, Serengeti/Ngorongoro safari), no duplicates, app served.\n- R12 · step 2 · L1 · `user-thing/thing#path-3-and-path-4-consent` + `organize_material/01-inventory` · verify=FAIL · organizer-only replay invoked the tasklist and built every required leg, but over-fragmented into 11 specialists and left `appManifest.built=false`; next round must diagnose tasklist inventory/app handoff rather than restoring duplicate direct calls.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":70,"oldLines":4,"newStart":70,"newLines":4,"lines":["   still shows a genuine parallel-clobber). Context death is fixed (compact `step-NN.json`), so ONE","   clean `--through 2` verify should finish: expect ONE specialist per leg (Cairo, Dar, Zanzibar/Stone","   Town, Serengeti/Ngorongoro safari), no duplicates, app served.","-- R12 · step 2 · L1 · `user-thing/thing#path-3-and-path-4-consent` + `organize_material/01-inventory` · verify=FAIL · organizer-only replay invoked the tasklist and built every required leg, but over-fragmented into 11 specialists and left `appManifest.built=false`; next round must diagnose tasklist inventory/app handoff rather than restoring duplicate direct calls.","+- R12 · step 2 · L1 · `user-thing/thing#path-3-and-path-4-consent` + `organize_material/01-inventory` · verify=FAIL · organizer-only replay invoked the tasklist but attempt 3 over-fragmented into 11 specialists and attempt 4 still created 8 off-partition specialists with `appManifest.built=false`; next round must diagnose tasklist inventory/app handoff rather than restoring duplicate direct calls."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
